rComments: Professor Subtelny is one of the best in her field. Her lectures are always clear, and I loved her class. It's been almost a year since I finished her class, and I still miss it to this very day.

Best professor I've come across during my time at U of T. She is very passionate about the courses she teaches and most helpful should you need any aid. Very interesting woman overall, and I enjoyed her course immensely!
Discourteous and unhelpful. Has limited knowledge about certain subjects. Excellent course but extremely disappointed with the professor.

AMAZING CLASS. She is extremely enthusiastic about the subject and present it beautifully in a way that you will remember for the rest of your life. Assignments have clear guidelines and are reasonable. Learned so much in her class, and didnt even need to study for the tests.

Prof. Subtelny is a rare breed of professors who not only brings a great wealth of information to the class but makes it fascinating even if, like myself, the class isn't your cup of tea. She graded everything herself for this class and returned assignments on time. If you take good notes exams and essays are a breeze. One of the best profs Ive had
She pretends to be nice, but cares, primarily, for her CV not the students.

I have known this professor for 2 years now. She is very passionate about her work. She is very compassionate. She is very kind and helpful, if you ask for it.  Her course requirements meet the standards of a prestigious university , however, her grading is very fair and encouraging.
She pretends that she is very nice, but she is not. Do not trust her.She is the worst professor ever. Avoid her!
I was a student of maria's in 1980. I remember her with great fondness. A person of deep loveliness and she could also share her knowledge.
She is great. But TAs...another story. Work hard on the essays, and find past exams...its exactly the SAME! Easy A.

Took this course as an elective, ended up loving it. She is very organized and professional. Uses outlines for lectures but additional notes are a must. The essays are based on readings so much of what you learn in class isnt tested until the exam. I didnt study and simply recounted what I had learned in class - pulled an A. Great prof, fun course.
Excellent Professor!! Excellent course: SRV Classical Persian Poetry. She is Lovely too.

Excellent. Never met a prof SO passionate about her work. Encourages and engages students to think for themselves. The class was phenomenally good in orienting my writing skills and just understanding theology more acutely, through use of several sources.

I took a first year seminar called "Islamic and Jewish Mysticism" with Ms. Subtelny. She is possibly one of the best professors I've had, and is very interested and informed on her subject matter. If you are honestly interested you will learn a lot from her.
Her classes were awesome. She held the only history class I did not sleep in them.
she has a tremendous grasp of the material, her insights are amazing. it was an overall pleasure to study with her. very approachable.
